page.title: 10King's Wood,Totteridge,Bucks
page.content: {King's Wood}consists of 185 acres of woodland approx. 1 x 0.25 miles. Chepping Wycombe Parish Council bought it for Â£850 in 1922. It appears in {Bassetsbury Manor's}records over 400 years ago, but could be older. Trees are mainly Beech and Oak. The woodland borders consist of scrubland where grasses, clover, buttercups, thistles and stinging nettles grow, also dog rose bushes and elderberry. Underneath the trees the undergrowth depends upon the amount of light filtering through the tree canopy. Where enough light reaches, grasses proliferate with common wild flowers. Other woods are {Pughs}12.5 acres,{Brook}7.8 acres, {Common}and{Larches}204.5 acres,{Pond 0.27 acres,{Coppice Hoop}8.52 acres, Longfield 5.57 acres,{Gatemoor}2.86 acres,{Magpie}10.8 acres{Twichels}4.5 acres and{Vicarage}3.5 acres.
